—to involve a wider spectrum of thoughtful and interested foreign
                            individuals and institutions in a discussion involving clear statements
                            of the U.S. positions and policies;

—to help develop a broader based consensus in other countries in support
                            of U.S. positions; but at a minimum, to bring more serious and realistic
                            public deliberations to bear on the several issues;

—regional seminars and conferences bringing together leading
                            intellectuals for realistic discussions of arms control and disarmament
                            issues;
